(fifthQuint)Effect of Intravenous Lidocaine and Dexamethasone Combination on Postoperative Sore Throat, Cough and Hoarseness.

.

 Sore throat and hoarseness following tracheal intubation are common postoperative problems causing dissatisfaction and discomfort to the patients.

 Their incidence varies from 30%-70%.

 Both non pharmacological and pharmacological measures have been tried to minimize the incidence and severity of POST with variable success rate.

 Prophylactic use lidocaine and steroids have been used independently for this purpose.

 Dexamethasone as an adjuvant to lidocaine has shown to improve the quality of analgesia.

 However, there is no study assessing the combine effects of lidocaine and dexamethasone for POST.

